%20country%3A%20You%20better%20start%20packing%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAuthorities%20estimate%20that%20some%2011%20million%20people%20are%20living%20in%20the%20United%20States%20illegally.%20Trump's%20deportation%20plan%20is%20expected%20directly%20to%20impact%20around%2020%20million%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20US%20government%20has%20struggled%20for%20years%20to%20manage%20its%20southern%20border%20with%20Mexico%2C%20Trump%20has%20super-charged%20concerns%20by%20claiming%20an%20%26quot%3Binvasion%26quot%3B%20is%20underway%20by%20migrants%20he%20says%20will%20rape%20and%20murder%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20campaign%2C%20Trump%20repeatedly%20railed%20against%20undocumented%20immigrants%2C%20employing%20incendiary%20rhetoric%20about%20foreigners%20who%20%26quot%3Bpoison%20the%20blood%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20United%20States%20and%20misleading%20his%20audiences%20about%20immigration%20statistics%20and%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20not%20elaborated%20on%20his%20immigration%20crackdown%20in%20any%20detail%20but%20during%20his%20election%20campaign%20repeatedly%20vowed%20to%20invoke%20the%20Alien%20Enemies%20Act%20of%201798%20to%20speed%20up%20deportations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECritics%20say%20the%20law%20is%20outdated%20and%20point%20to%20its%20most%20recent%20use%20during%20World%20War%20II%20to%20hold%20Japanese-Americans%20in%20internment%20camps%20without%20due%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20US%20border%20patrol%20encounters%20with%20migrants%20crossing%20from%20Mexico%20illegally%20is%20now%20about%20the%20same%20as%20in%202020%2C%20the%20last%20year%20of%20Trump's%20first%20term%2C%20after%20peaking%20at%20a%20record%20250%2C000%20for%20the%20month%20of%20December%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22