0Goldman%20Sachs%20and%20Morgan%20Stanley%20%E2%80%94%20but%20banking%20felt%20novel%20and%20challenging%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20job%20out%20of%20school%20was%20at%20DBS%20Bank%2C%20where%20I%20did%20corporate%20foreign%20exchange%20sales.%20I%20was%20an%20engineering%20graduate%20and%20not%20as%20savvy%20as%20my%20colleagues%2C%20who%20majored%20in%20business%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20two%20years%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20leave%20DBS%20and%20get%20my%20master's%20in%20finance%20at%20Lancaster%20University.%20I%20wasn't%20able%20to%20secure%20a%20job%20in%20London%2C%20though.%20I%20ended%20up%20returning%20to%20Singapore%20in%20the%20thick%20of%20the%201997%20Asian%20Financial%20Crisis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20jobs%20were%20scarce%2C%20I%20decided%20to%20take%20work%20in%20risk%20management%20instead.%20That%20was%20when%20I%20joined%20Standard%20Chartered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20fortunate%20to%20have%20a%20good%20boss.%20He%20really%20believed%20in%20me%20and%20sent%20me%20on%20secondments%20to%20London%20and%20Hong%20Kong.%20That%20kickstarted%20my%20international%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20later%20moved%20on%20to%20Citibank%20in%202001%2C%20where%20I%20worked%20on%20global%20markets.%20In%202005%2C%20I%20saw%20that%20China%20was%20liberalizing%20its%20financial%20sector%2C%20so%20I%20asked%20my%20boss%20to%20post%20me%20to%20China%2C%20and%20I%20spent%20two%20years%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20in%20China%20was%20eye-opening.%20Compared%20to%20a%20small%20country%20like%20Singapore%2C%20there%20were%20lots%20more%20industries%2C%20such%20as%20mining%20and%20shipping%2C%20to%20cover.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20then%20relocated%20to%20Hong%20Kong%20and%20switched%20my%20focus%20to%20investment%20banking%20and%20Asia-centric%20transactions.%20That%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20me%20to%20join%20UBS%20as%20a%20managing%20director.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226126e89b-83ba-409f-829f-7c6830f6f066%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20can%20play%20the%20game%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20enjoy%20the%20game%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Eric%20Sim%20giving%20a%20lecture%20to%20students.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d813be1d8d2deb96b87ac7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESim%20left%20UBS%20in%202017%20and%20is%20now%20a%20professional%20speaker%20and%20executive%20coach.%20In%202021%2C%20he%20co-authored%20a%20book%20on%20career%20guidance%2C%20%26quot%3BSmall%20Actions.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EEric%20Sim%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20honest%2C%20I've%20always%20thought%20of%20leaving%20banking.%20Back%20in%202005%2C%20I%20thought%20of%20returning%20to%20college%20to%20study%20architecture.%20I%20applied%20for%20a%20spot%20and%20got%20accepted%20into%20the%20program%20after%20passing%20a%20test.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20decided%20against%20it.%20If%20I%20went%20back%20to%20school%2C%20I%20would%20have%20to%20study%20for%20five%20years%20and%20accrue%20two%20years%20of%20practical%20experience%20before%20I%20could%20qualify%20as%20an%20architect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20a%20huge%20opportunity%20cost%20for%20me%2C%20as%20I%20would%20have%20made%20well%20over%20a%20million%20dollars%20if%20I%20had%20stayed%20with%20banking%20during%20the%20same%20period.%20I%20was%20in%20my%20mid-thirties%20then%2C%20and%20I%20still%20had%20to%20pay%20my%20mortgage.%20It%20didn't%20make%20financial%20sense%20to%20leave%20banking%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20said%2C%20I%20also%20recognized%20that%20while%20I%20could%20play%20the%20game%2C%20I%20didn't%20enjoy%20it.%20For%20most%20people%20who%20go%20into%20banking%2C%20the%20norm%20is%20to%20work%20as%20much%20as%20you%20can%20and%20retire%20when%20you're%2060.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20that%20leaves%20you%20with%20very%20limited%20choices%20in%20life.%20Your%20health%20may%20deteriorate%2C%20and%20you%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20travel%20as%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20after%20spending%20over%2020%20years%20in%20banking%2C%20I%20left%20UBS%20in%202017.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20point%2C%20my%20health%20was%20still%20good%2C%20and%20I%20had%20sufficient%20savings.%20That%20meant%20that%20I%20could%20pursue%20the%20things%20I%20liked%20and%20start%20a%20new%20career%20in%20professional%20speaking%20and%20executive%20coaching.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20phase%20of%20my%20life%2C%20I'm%20now%20focusing%20on%20satisfaction%2C%20meaning%2C%20and%20fulfillment.%20Through%20my%20work%20as%20a%20speaker%20and%20lecturer%2C%20I%20have%20been%20able%20to%20share%20my%20know-how%20in%20banking%20and%20career%20planning%20with%20more%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22cd01a843-0073-4c6f-b1d9-e32d59c1e82f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20is%20a%20lot%20harder%20to%20make%20it%20in%20banking%20these%20days%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Eric%20Sim%20standing%20in%20front%20of%20the%20London%20Bridge.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d6d3a214a5cd1fcc8c89fa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWhen%20Sim%20graduated%20from%20Lancaster%20University%20in%201997%20with%20his%20master's%20in%20finance%2C%20he%20couldn't%20find%20a%20job%20in%20London.%3Cp%3EEric%20Sim%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBanking%20is%20really%20just%20a%20sales%20job.%20It%20is%20about%20knowing%20what%20your%20customer%20wants%20and%20then%20building%20a%20relationship.%20You%20want%20to%20be%20the%20first%20person%20the%20client%20calls%20when%20they%20have%20a%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20succeeding%20in%20banking%20is%20a%20lot%20harder%20these%20days.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20there%20was%20less%20competition%20and%20less%20regulation%20within%20the%20sector.%20It%20was%20easier%20for%20the%20banks%20to%20make%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThings%20are%20different%20now.%20After%20the%202008%20Global%20Financial%20Crisis%2C%20a%20lot%20more%20people%20now%20know%20how%20much%20money%20bankers%20can%20make.%20There%20is%20a%20lot%20more%20competition%20for%20banking%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20if%20I%20could%20turn%20the%20clock%20back%2C%20I%20would%20still%20pick%20banking%20as%20a%20career.%20Banking%20is%20an%20excellent%20industry%20for%20self-development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20advice%20to%20young%20professionals%20is%20to%20seek%20out%20job%20opportunities%20that%20allow%20them%20to%20learn.%20That%20has%20been%20my%20career%20principle%20and%20it%20has%20served%20me%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmd-ubs-17-years-banking-quit-work-life-balance-2024-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731973321000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66d6b7dd289b805d1db377e3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmd-ubs-17-years-banking-quit-work-life-balance-2024-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Eric%20Sim%2C%2054%2C%20spent%20more%20than%2020%20years%20in%20banking.%20The%20former%20UBS%20managing%20director%20now%20works%20as%20a%20professional%20speaker%20and%20executive%20coach.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ktan%40businessinsider.com%20(Kwan%20Wei%20Kevin%20Tan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A27%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmd-ubs-17-years-banking-quit-work-life-balance-2024-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Robin%20Williams%20Called%20Conan%20O%E2%80%99Brien%20After%20%E2%80%98Tonight%20Show%E2%80%99%20Firing%20and%20Sent%20Him%20Out%20on%20a%20Bike%20Ride%3A%20%E2%80%98You%E2%80%99re%20Gonna%20Be%20Fine.%20Ride%20Around%20Around%2C%20You%E2%80%99ll%20Feel%20Better%E2%80%99%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731972005000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp