0%2C000%20and%20wounded%20at%20around%20400%2C000.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Russia%20and%20Ukraine%20have%20diminishing%20populations%20and%20have%20been%20struggling%20from%20even%20before%20the%20war.%20The%20staggering%20death%20count%20due%20to%20the%20war%20will%20thereby%20have%20far-reaching%20demographic%20implications%20for%20both%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECIVILIAN%20DEATHS%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20roughly%20million%20casualties%20account%20mostly%20for%20soldiers%20and%20military%20personnel%2C%20the%20civilian%20casualties%20in%20Ukraine%20as%20of%20August%2031%2C%202024%20are%20documented%20to%20be%20at%20least%2011%2C743%20killed%20and%2024%2C614%20wounded.%20These%20figures%20are%20as%20per%20the%20UN%20Human%20Rights%20Monitoring%20Mission%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20United%20Nations%20and%20Ukrainian%20officials%20say%20that%20the%20real%20number%20of%20deaths%20and%20injuries%20are%20like%20to%20be%20far%20more%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20verify%20the%20deaths%20and%20injuries%2C%20especially%20in%20areas%20such%20as%20Mariupol%20that%20are%20now%20in%20Russian%20hands.%20589%20Ukrainian%20children%20have%20also%20been%20killed%20till%20November%2014%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2F92h0hu14_russia-ukraine-war-afp_625x300_19_November_24.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20Reuters%20report%2C%20tens%20of%20thousands%20have%20perished%20in%20intense%20fighting%20across%20heavily%20fortified%20front%20lines%20under%20relentless%20artillery%20fire%2C%20with%20tanks%2C%20armoured%20vehicles%20and%20infantry%20mounting%20assaults%20on%20trenches.%20The%20report%20also%20states%20that%20both%20sides%20closely%20guard%20tallies%20of%20their%20own%20military%20losses%20as%20national%20security%20secrets%2C%20and%20public%20estimates%20by%20Western%20countries%20based%20on%20intelligence%20reports%20vary%20widely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20estimates%20that%20Russia%20has%20suffered%20great%20losses%20too%20in%20terms%20of%20military%20deaths%2C%20accounting%20for%20more%20than%20a%201%2C000%20dead%20soldiers%20per%20day%20during%20intense%20periods%20of%20the%20war.%20Ukraine's%20President%20Zelensky%20had%20said%20in%20February%2C%202024%20that%20more%20than%2031%2C000%20Ukrainian%20service%20members%20had%20been%20killed%2C%20which%20analysts%20believe%20is%20a%20very%20conservative%20estimate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20war%20has%20also%20led%20to%20Ukraine's%20birthrate%20to%20fall%20to%20a%20third%20of%20what%20it%20used%20to%20be%202.5%20years%20ago%2C%20before%20the%20war%20began.%20While%20more%20than%20four%20million%20people%20have%20been%20displaced%20within%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20war%20has%20also%20led%20to%20more%20than%20six%20million%20Ukrainian%20nationals%20fleeing%20abroad%20-%20mostly%20to%20European%20countries.%20Not%20only%20has%20Ukraine's%20mortality%20rate%20from%20causes%20other%20than%20the%20war%20surged%20since%20the%20conflict%20began%2C%20UN%20estimates%20suggest%20that%20Ukraine's%20population%20has%20declined%20by%20over%2010%20million%20people%2C%20which%20is%20around%20a%20quarter%20of%20its%20overall%20population%2C%20suggesting%20that%2025%20percent%20of%20the%20population%20has%20been%20wiped%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ETERRITORY%20LOST%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%20now%20occupies%20and%20claims%20to%20have%20annexed%20around%20a%20fifth%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20an%20area%20around%20the%20size%20of%20Greece%2C%20news%20agency%20Reuters%20reported.%20Moscow's%20forces%20initially%20stormed%20through%20northern%2C%20eastern%20and%20southern%20Ukraine%20in%20early%202022%2C%20reaching%20the%20outskirts%20of%20Kyiv%20in%20the%20north%20and%20crossing%20the%20Dnipro%20River%20in%20the%20south%2C%20it%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoscow%20has%20even%20captured%20nearly%20the%20whole%20of%20the%20Donbas%20region%20in%20Ukraine's%20east%2C%20and%20the%20entire%20coast%20of%20the%20Sea%20of%20Azov%20in%20the%20south.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Reuters%20report%2C%20many%20cities%20in%20the%20frontline%20area%20that%20have%20been%20captured%20by%20Moscow%20have%20been%20destroyed%2C%20largest%20among%20them%20the%20Azov%20port%20of%20Mariupol%2C%20with%20a%20population%20before%20the%20war%20of%20around%20half%20a%20million.%20In%20the%20past%20year%2C%20Russia%20has%20slowly%20extended%20its%20grip%20in%20intense%20fighting%2C%20mainly%20in%20the%20Donbas.%20Ukraine%2C%20for%20its%20part%2C%20launched%20its%20first%20large-scale%20assault%20on%20Russian%20territory%20in%20August%20and%20has%20captured%20a%20sliver%20of%20western%20Russia's%20Kursk%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EECONOMIC%20IMPACT%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20Ukraine's%20economy%20shrunk%20by%20nearly%20a%20third%20(33%20per%20cent)%20of%20what%20it%20used%20to%20be%20before%20the%20war.%20In%202023%20however%2C%20the%20war-torn%20country%20made%20a%20marginal%20comeback%20and%20managed%20to%20reduce%20the%20economic%20losses%20to%20roughly%2022%20per%20cent%20of%20its%20original%20size.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20a%20Reuters%20report%2C%20the%20latest%20available%20assessment%20by%20the%20World%20Bank%2C%20European%20Commission%2C%20United%20Nations%20and%20Ukrainian%20government%20found%20that%20direct%20war%20damage%20in%20Ukraine%20had%20reached%20%24152%20billion%20as%20of%20December%2C%202023%2C%20with%20housing%2C%20transport%2C%20commerce%20and%20industry%2C%20energy%20and%20agriculture%20the%20worst-affected%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20total%20cost%20of%20reconstruction%20and%20recovery%20was%20estimated%20by%20the%20World%20Bank%20and%20Ukrainian%20government%20at%20%24486%20billion%20as%20of%20the%20end%20of%20December%20last%20year.%20The%20figure%20is%202.8%20times%20higher%20than%20Ukraine's%20nominal%20gross%20domestic%20product%20in%202023%2C%20according%20to%20economy%20ministry%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUkraine's%20power%20sector%20has%20been%20particularly%20hard%20hit%2C%20with%20Russia%20regularly%20targeting%20infrastructure%20in%20long%20range%20attacks.%20Ukraine%20is%20also%20one%20of%20the%20world's%20main%20sources%20of%20grain%2C%20and%20the%20interruption%20of%20its%20exports%20early%20in%20the%20war%20worsened%20a%20global%20food%20crisis.%20Exports%20have%20since%20largely%20recovered%20with%20Ukraine%20finding%20ways%20to%20circumvent%20a%20de%20facto%20Russian%20blockade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20day%20the%20war%20is%20costing%20Kyiv%20more%20than%20%24140%20million%2C%20Roksolana%20Pidlasa%2C%20head%20of%20Ukraine%20parliament's%20budget%20committee%2C%20said.%20The%20draft%202025%20budget%20envisages%20that%20about%2026%25%20of%20Ukraine's%20GDP%2C%20or%202.2%20trillion%20hryvnias%20(%2453.3%20billion)%2C%20would%20go%20on%20defence.%20Ukraine%20has%20already%20received%20more%20than%20%24100%20billion%20from%20its%20Western%20partners%20in%20financial%20aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20we%20know%20today%20as%20Ukraine%20was%20once%20part%20of%20the%20Russian%20Empire%20and%20subsequently%20also%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20till%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20USSR%20in%201991.%20Vladimir%20Putin%20has%20said%20on%20multiple%20occasions%20that%20he%20seeks%20to%20revert%20Ukraine%20back%20to%20the%20Russian%20Federation.%20President%20Putin%20has%20denied%20recognition%20to%20Ukrainian%20identity%20and%20statehood%20and%20claims%20that%20the%20people%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20who%20are%20mostly%20Slavic%20or%20Orthodox%20Christians%2C%20are%20in%20fact%20Russian%20people.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731969060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%